Description: Tondo sherd of Attic black-figured pottery cup, probably of type A; interior: wall glazed; glaze band at edge of tondo which preserves black-figure decoration consisting perhaps of male head to left; exterior: glazed with two reserved bands.
Curator's comments: There are deposits on the interioer, exterior and edges of the sherd.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GA.0635) (Phase 1)
